Paragraph:
SVCs are monoclausal units with two or more verbs conjoined without any
conjunction;ii. SVCs are contiguous constructions as no constituents except arguments may
intervene between the verbs;
iii. SVCs have intonational properties of a mono-verbal clause (Givón, 1990);
iv. verbs in SVCs may share their inflections, especially for aspect;
v. verbs in SVCs share negation;
vi. verbs in SVCs share at least one argument.
